<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-48-0580 </DOCNO><TEXT>An expert system is discussed which assists in deciding the deicing countermeasuresagainst snow accretion on 187KV and 66KV transmission lines. The distinctivefeatures of the system are the application of an expert system to a newfield, the completely hierarchical design of the whole system and rankingby messages instead of by a certainty factor. The system has been developedas a prototype using micro-PROLOG and is under trial use in real powersystem operations.</TEXT></DOC>